      • getPacketPayloadSize

        public int getPacketPayloadSize()

        Returns:
        the packet payload size

      • getFECEncodingID

        public int getFECEncodingID()
        The FEC encoding ID is subject to IANA registration (see RFC 3452). Note that - value zero corresponds to the "Compact No-Code FEC scheme" also known as "Null-FEC" (RFC 3695); - value one corresponds to the "MBMS FEC" (3GPP TS 26.346); - for values in the range of 0 to 127, inclusive, the FEC scheme is Fully-Specified, whereas for values in the range of 128 to 255, inclusive, the FEC scheme is Under-Specified.
        Returns:
        the FEC encoding ID

      • getFECInstanceID

        public int getFECInstanceID()
        The FEC instance ID provides a more specific identification of the FEC encoder being used for an Under-Specified FEC scheme. This value should be set to zero for Fully-Specified FEC schemes and shall be ignored when parsing a file with an FEC encoding ID in the range of 0 to 127, inclusive. The FEC instance ID is scoped by the FEC encoding ID. See RFC 3452 for further details.
        Returns:
        the FEC instance ID

      • getEncodingSymbolLength

        public int getEncodingSymbolLength()
        The encoding symbol length gives the size (in bytes) of one encoding symbol. All encoding symbols of one item have the same length, except the last symbol which may be shorter.
        Returns:
        the encoding symbol length

      • getMaxNumberOfEncodingSymbols

        public int getMaxNumberOfEncodingSymbols()
        The maximum number of encoding symbols that can be generated for a source block for those FEC schemes in which the maximum number of encoding symbols is relevant, such as FEC encoding ID 129 defined in RFC 3452. For those FEC schemes in which the maximum number of encoding symbols is not relevant, the semantics of this field is unspecified.
        Returns:
        the maximum number of encoding symbols

      • getSchemeSpecificInfo

        public java.lang.String getSchemeSpecificInfo()
        The scheme specific info is a String of the scheme-specific object transfer information (FEC-OTI-Scheme-Specific-Info). The definition of the information depends on the EC encoding ID.
        Returns:
        the scheme specific info

      • getBlockCounts

        public int[] getBlockCounts()
        A block count indicates the number of consecutive source blocks with a specified size.
        Returns:
        all block counts

      • getBlockSizes

        public long[] getBlockSizes()
        A block size indicates the size of a block (in bytes). A block_size that is not a multiple of the encoding symbol length indicates with Compact No-Code FEC that the last source symbols includes padding that is not stored in the item. With MBMS FEC (3GPP TS 26.346) the padding may extend across multiple symbols but the size of padding should never be more than the encoding symbol length.
        Returns:
        all block sizes
